        <div class="container">
        <header class="header">
        <h1>About MIS Quarterly</h1>
        </header>
        <section class="mission-vision-section">
        <div class="mission-card">
        <h2>Editorial Mission</h2>
        <p>Our editorial mission is the enhancement and communication of knowledge concerning the development of IT-based services, the management of IT resources, and the use, impact, and economics of IT with managerial, organizational, and societal implications.</p>
        <p>Professional issues affecting the IS field as a whole are also in the purview of the journal.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="vision-card">
        <h2>Vision</h2>
        <p>MIS Quarterly's vision is to publish the finest information systems scholarship. This was the original vision of the publication's founders in 1977 and continues serving as a unified objective for both the publication's Editor-in-Chief and Editorial Board.</p>
        <div class="vision-links">
        <p>For a better understanding of how our vision has evolved over the years:</p>
        <a href="https://misq.umn.edu/misq/article/40/1/iii/1556/Editor-s-CommentsThe-MIS-Quarterly-Trifecta-Impact?searchresult=1">Opening Editorial by former Editor-in-Chief Arun Rai</a>
        <a href="/DocumentLibrary/MiscDocs/00_iii_edcomments_v45_1.pdf" target="_blank">Opening Editorial by former Editor-in-Chief Andrew Burton-Jones</a>
        </div>
        </div>
        </section>
        <section class="framework-section">
        <div class="framework-title">
        <h2>Our Framework for Excellence</h2>
        <p class="framework-subtitle">Meaningful research is driven by real world impact. We have defined 3 core considerations for papers seeking publication in MISQ:</p>
        </div>
        <div class="framework-diagram">
        <div class="pillar">
        <span class="pillar-number">1</span>
        <h3>Scholarly Contribution</h3>
        <p>The research pursues answers that impart significant contribution to the IS discipline.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar">
        <span class="pillar-number">2</span>
        <h3>Practical Utility</h3>
        <p>The research enables a broader impact on business and society.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar">
        <span class="pillar-number">3</span>
        <h3>Aesthetics</h3>
        <p>The research achieves "powerful simplicity", whether mathematical or qualitative, in its answer.</p>
        </div>
        </div>
        <div class="excellence-formula">
        <h3>The MISQ Standard</h3>
        <div class="formula">Scholarly Contribution + Practical Utility + Aesthetics = MISQ Excellence</div>
        <p>An ideal contribution to MISQ is one that answers the question utilizing all three dimensions.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="interdisciplinary-note">
        <h4>Interdisciplinary Research Welcome</h4>
        <p>Interdisciplinary papers are also welcomed at MISQ, with the expectation they highlight the role of IS in the formulation of the problem and consequently in the contribution.</p>
        <p>Authors are encouraged to read the following editorial to understand MISQ expectations on contributions and common errors in formulating IS research problems: <a href="https://misq.umn.edu/misq/article/41/2/iii/334/Editor-s-CommentsAvoiding-Type-III-Errors?searchresult=1">Avoiding Type III Errors: Formulating IS Research Problems that Matter</a>.</p>
        </div>
        </section>
        <section class="impact-metrics">
        <h3>Our Impact &amp; Recognition</h3>
        <div class="metrics-grid">
        <div class="metric-item">
